    The code for changing the color to any other is exactly the same, except you change the numbers for the RGB value.  When you have elements in CSS that both change the same thing, the code that is the most nested in the HTML will override the other codes.  Another way to think about it is the more specific you are in which tag that you assign a value to, the more power it will have to override other values from other tags. In addition, if there isn’t a value given in the more nested tags, the outermost tag in the HTML code with a value for the element will be used.
